{
  "texts": [
    "It also examined deceptive techniques such as honeypots, which organizations could employ to find new exploits.Researchers examined the use of the dark web in cybercrime, including stolen datasets, compromised email accounts, and breached credentials, as well as hiring cyberattack botnets [21].",
    "In addition, it discussed how to protect small and medium-sized businesses (SMEs) and microenterprises (MEs) against the threats posed by these activities.",
    "As part of this process, businesses must monitor the dark web for any mentions or discussions of their company or industry and stay up-to-date on any new attack methods or tools that cybercriminals use.",
    "In addition, according to the paper, businesses should prioritize protecting their email accounts since email is often the primary way cybercriminals gain access to sensitive data.Because healthcare holds sensitive information, including protected healthcare information (PHI), it is a high-value target for cyberattacks [22].",
    "A breach of patient privacy affects not only the privacy of patients but also the reputation and ability to operate healthcare organizations."
  ]
}